name: market for lean concrete | lean concrete | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/12880/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'lean concrete', in the Global geography.;In this market, expert judgement was used to develop product specific transport distance estimations.;The product "lean concrete" may be produced from cement CEM II/A or CEM II/B. Density: 2250 kg/m3, content of cement: 150 kg/m3. Exposition class according to EN 206-1: no normative requirements. This product is used for blinding layers below foundations.

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'lean concrete',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of 'lean concrete',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.
